objects.name: wishful woodchuck
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck is a non-persistent Windows keylogger that logs keystrokes to a file on disk named msimm.dat. It uses Windows API calls to hook the keyboard and obfuscates the log file using a multi-byte rotating XOR key embedded in the binary. It does not contain persistence or network communications functionality. The malware has been observed in both x86 and x64 variants, sometimes dropped by an executable like msvrt.exe. It shares some characteristics with malware used by the Turla threat group, such as XOR 0x55 obfuscation of function names and the use of a 'TVer' versioning string.

objects.name: Turla
objects.description: A threat group associated with the Wishful Woodchuck keylogger. The malware uses techniques previously observed in Turla's tools, including the use of a 'TVer' versioning string in its log file and encoding Windows API function names with XOR 0x55.

objects.name: Input Capture: Keylogging
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck uses Windows API calls to log keystrokes

objects.name: Obfuscated Files or Information
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck uses multi-byte XOR obfuscation of strings in its binary and log file

objects.name: Obfuscated Files or Information

objects.name: Masquerading: Match Legitimate Name or Location
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck uses a filename (lmm32.dll) similar to a legitimate Windows signed binary (imm32.dll)

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Finds binaries containing the hardcoded XOR key
from the keylogger binaries"

    strings:
        $xorkey = {0A 19 59 2D 6C 59 6F FA 8B 6F 9B FF 37 9B BD 7B 59 4B
7B DD 0F 64 91 C7 D6 9C 6F 7B 9C 01 9C 91 79 C7 C8 C9 DF E1 FA FF 04 08
59 E6 64 6D 37 9B 38 81 2D 81 65 7D 66 9A}

    condition:

uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
all of them

}

        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Unique file description"

strings:

$description = "Multi-User Windows IMM32 API CIient DLL" wide

condition:

uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
all of them

}

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_logfile_encodedheader
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule wishfulwoodchuck_logfile_encodedheader
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Encoded log file header"

    strings:
        $header = {41 19 0A 2D 20 59 5F FA 81 6F CF FF 61 9B D8 7B 2B 4B
46}
    condition:
        all of them
}
